# Core Events Context

You are changing cross-domain runtime event contracts (event-port interfaces and runtime hubs).

Read these docs:

1. `docs/design/core-architecture.md` — EventBus pattern + current/planned runtime event contract
2. `docs/design/README.md` — domain routing index to load only affected system docs
3. `docs/design/extensible-development-contracts.md` — cross-domain extension guardrails for event hub/wiring/save integration
4. `docs/design/inventory-and-economy.md` when adding/changing inventory event contracts (`OnItemPickupRequested`, `OnItemStored`, `OnItemPickupRejected`, `OnBeltSelectionChanged`, `OnInventoryChanged`)
5. `docs/design/weapons-and-ballistics.md` when adding/changing weapon/shooting event contracts (`OnWeaponEquipped`, `OnWeaponFired`, `OnWeaponReloaded`, `OnProjectileHit`)
6. `docs/design/world-scene-contracts.md` when event changes touch interaction hints, travel, or scene-level interaction wiring

If an event shape change affects a domain payload/restore boundary, also load:

7. `docs/design/save-contract-quick-reference.md`
8. `docs/design/save-and-progression.md`

When adding new event groups or moving event-contract files across `Core/Scripts/Events` and `Core/Scripts/Runtime`, keep this router globs aligned in the same change.
